        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 2:09PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 208 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 3
miles southeast of Vale, or 14 miles northeast of Sturgis, moving
northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Vale and Owl Butte.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm is producing large quantities of hail. Driving through
deep hail is like driving on slushy roads. Slow down and do not brake
suddenly.</instruction>
